messages.message: Happy monday :slightly_smiling_face: I’ve spotted a few times now that aihub has misunderstood my question when asking for a json (Prod, GPT 3.5) (also that chart isn’t right)

Prompts:
`Return the information from the document as a json {year, revenue}`
`Return as a json {year, revenue}`
`Translate this into japanese ```{year, revenue}````
I’m attaching both the english and japanese version so its easier to debug, but bug is happenign on JP one
@Prakhar looks like these queries are incorrectly classified as visualisation queries. Can we check why it's happening with these prompts?
Yeah, its incorrect query classification. Checking!
@Gwen to unblock you -- for extraction, please use Build. We don't do intent classification there, so you can avoid errors like this.
